description: Reuters journalist covering stocks, options and FX https://t.co/H9krKZ4J9Y tips/notes to saqib.ahmed@tr.com
tweets: Historically, you were better off waiting 3 months from the market bottom than you were if you started buying even 1 month too soon.  Of course this is only on avg. Might not apply always. 5/5

name: Saqib
description: Reuters journalist covering stocks, options and FX https://t.co/H9krKZ4J9Y tips/notes to saqib.ahmed@tr.com
tweets:
Call the bear market bottom just 1 month too soon and the 1-year return will have shrunk to 22%. And if by some ill luck you were to have started buying 3 months before the bottom was in, your 1-year return, on average, while still positive, is a dismal 8%.
  4/5

name: Saqib
description: Reuters journalist covering stocks, options and FX https://t.co/H9krKZ4J9Y tips/notes to saqib.ahmed@tr.com
tweets:
Wait even longer, say 3-months from the bear market bottom before starting to buy, and your 1-year return would on average, shrink to 23%.
    So, clearly there is value in being on time or being patient in turning bullish. But what about being too early? 
 3/5

name: Saqib
description: Reuters journalist covering stocks, options and FX https://t.co/H9krKZ4J9Y tips/notes to saqib.ahmed@tr.com
tweets:
If you called each of the bottoms for the last 10 bear markets perfectly, in a year, on average, you would have been up 44%.
    If you called it just 1 month too late, the 1-year return would have been cut 17 percentage points to 27%.

2/5

name: Saqib
